and 3 probable), bringing the total to 1,445 (1,107 confirmed and 338 probable). NZ authorities also report 32 new recoveries, bringing the total to 1,006. The country also reports a new death, bringing the death toll to 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=21 April 2020|access-date=21 April 2020|archive-date=21 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200421015622/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2020/04/coronavirus-five-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-new-zealand.html|first=Jamie|last=Ensor|title=Coronavirus: One death, five new cases of COVID-19 in New Zealand|work=Newshub|date=21 April 2020|accessdate=21 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200421020106/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2020/04/coronavirus-five-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-new-zealand.html|archive-date=21 April 2020}}</ref> In addition, a New Zealand traveller in Peru died after missing a repatriation flight, however this is not included in Ministry of Health figures.<ref name=\"NZ Herald Peru death\">{{cite news |last1=Henry |first1=Dubby |title=Covid 19 coronavirus: Kiwi, 49, found dead in Peru with Covid-19, family says |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12326247 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |work=[[New Zealand Herald]] |date=21 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200421002800/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12326247 |archivedate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Pakistan has confirmed 17 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 192. Pakistan also confirms 705 new cases, bringing the total to 9,214.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*The 