ion Report 93|last=|first=|date=|website=World Health Organization|url-status=live|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Bulgaria has reported a total number of 1,015 cases, 47 deaths, and 174 recoveries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bulgarian coronavirus cases pass 1,000, health ministry says |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2020/04/22/bulgarian-coronavirus-cases-pass-1000-health-ministry-says#cxrecs_s |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=22 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422105442/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2020/04/22/bulgarian-coronavirus-cases-pass-1000-health-ministry-says |archivedate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Canada has reported a total of 1,871 deaths and 38,932 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\">{{cite news |last1=Mayberry |first1=Kate |last2=Aziz |first2=Saba |last3=Allahoum |first3=Ramy |title=UN warns on hunger, as coronavirus cases top 2.5m: Live updates |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/warns-hunger-coronavirus-cases-top-25m-live-updates-200421233559829.html |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=22 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200423014822/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/warns-hunger-coronavirus-cases-top-25m-live-updates-200421233559829.html|archive-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*China has reported 30 new cases (23 involving people returning from overseas) and 42 asymptomatic cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Indonesia has reported 283 new cases, bringing the total to 7,418. Indonesia has also reported 19 deaths, bringing the death toll to 635. Indonesia has reported a total of 913 recoveries.<ref>{{cite news |title=Indonesia has 283 new Covid-19 cases and 19 deaths |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/04/22/indonesia-has-283-new-covid-19-cases-and-19-deaths#cxrecs_s |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422111838/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/04/22/indonesia-has-283-new-covid-19-cases-and-19-deaths |archivedate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Iran has reported 94 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 5,391. Iran has a total of 85,996 cases.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran coronavirus death toll rises by 94 to 5,391 - health ministry |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2020/04/22/iran-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-by-94-to-5391---health-ministry#cxrecs_s |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=22 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422113126/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/world/2020/04/22/iran-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-by-94-to-5391---health-ministry |archivedate=22 April 2020}}</ref> \n*Italy has reported 437 new deaths, bringing the death toll 25,085. Italian authorities have reported 3,370 cases, bringing the number of cases to 187,327.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*In Japan, [[Nagasaki]] authorities have confirmed 33 new cases aboard the Italian cruise ship ''[[Costa Atlantica]]'' based on contact tracing of an infected crew member. The ''Costa Atlantica'' has remained in Nagasaki's shipyard since February. Eight babies and children at a Tokyo-based residential care facility have tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Jordan has reported a total of 435 cases, 297 recoveries, and seven deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Lebanon has reported the death of a Syrian Palestinian at Wavel refugee camp in the eastern [[Bekaa Valley]].<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 50 new cases, bringing the total to 5,532. Malaysian health authorities have discharged 103 patients, bringing the total number of recoveries to 3,452. Malaysia reports one death, bringing the death toll to 93.<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19: 50 new cases, 103 recoveries, one new death takes fatalities to 93 |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/22/covid-19-50-new-cases-103-recovered-one-new-death-takes-fatalities-to-93 |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=22 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422101731/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/22/covid-19-50-new-cases-103-recovered-one-new-death-takes-fatalities-to-93 |archivedate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The Netherlands has confirmed 708 new cases, bringing the total to 34,842. Dutch health authorities have confirmed 138 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 4,054.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*New Zealand has reported six new cases, bringing the total to 1,451 (1,113 confirmed and 338 probable). In addition, there have been 30 new recoveries, bringing the total to 1,036. Authorities have also reported another death, bringing the death toll to 14.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=22 April 2020|access-date=22 April 2020|archive-date=22 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422012153/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Woman in her 80s dies of Covid-19, bringing New Zealand's death toll to 14 |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/woman-in-her-80s-dies-covid-19-bringing-new-zealands-death-toll-14|work=[[1 News]]|date=22 April 2020|accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The Philippines has reported 111 new cases, bringing the total number to 6,710. The Philippines has reported nine new deaths, bringing the total to 446. 39 patients have recovered, bringing the total number of recoveries to 693.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Qatar has reported 608 new cases, bringing the total number of cases to 7,141. Qatar health authorities have confirmed 75 recoveries and one new death.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Russia has reported 5,236 new cases, bringing the total to 57,999. Russia has reported 53 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 513.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Singapore has reported 1,016 new cases, bringing the total to 10,141. Another death was confirmed later, bringing the death toll to 12.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iau |first1=Jean |last2=Chong |first2=Clara |title=967 of 1,016 new coronavirus cases are foreign workers living in dormitories; 84-year-old S'porean woman is 12th person to die |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/1016-new-coronavirus-cases-take-singapore-tally-past-10000-mark |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=22 April 2020 |date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n*South Korea has reported 11 new cases (six involving overseas travel).<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Spain has reported 435 deaths, bringing the total to 21,717. The Spanish health ministry has reported 4,211 new cases, bringing the total to 208,389.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Switzerland has reported a total of 1,217 deaths and 28,268 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Turkey has reported 3,083 new cases, bringing the total number of cases to 98,674. The country has reported 117 new deaths, bringing the total to 2,376; 16,477 people have recovered and 37,535 people have been tested.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*Ukraine has reported a total of 6,592 cases, 174 deaths, and 424 recoveries.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*The United Kingdom has confirmed 763 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 18,100. The number of cases has reached 133,495. [[Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs|Foreign Secretary]] [[Dominic Raab]] has also confirmed the deaths of 69 [[National Health Service]] personnel as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*The United States has reported 1,738 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 46,583. Californian health authorities have also confirmed that two people in the state died from the coronavirus before the United States reported its first death in late February 2020.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n*According to [[John Hopkins University]], more than 2.5&nbsp;million people globally have contracted the coronavirus and at least 178,000 have died.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 22 April reports\" />\n\n===23 April===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 94:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200423-sitrep-94-covid-19.pdf?sfvrsn=b8304bf0_4|title=Situation Report 94|last=|first=|date=|website=World Health Organization|url-status=live|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n*China has reported ten new cases, bringing the total to 82,798. No new deaths have been reported.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 23 April reports\">{{cite news |last1=Rashid |first1=Zaheena |last2=Siddiqui |first2=Usaid |title=China reports 10 new coronavirus cases in mainland: Live updates |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/trump-downplays-threat-coronavirus-returning-live-updates-200423000536161.html |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Japan has reported 14 new cases aboard the Italian cruise ship ''[[Costa Atlantica]]'', bringing the total number of infected aboard the ship to 48. The ''Costa Atlantica'' is carrying 623 passengers.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 23 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 71 new cases, bringing the total number of cases to 5,603. 3,542 have recovered. Malaysia also reports two new deaths, bringing the death toll to 95.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaos, Jr |first1=Joseph |title=Covid-19 update: 71 new cases, 90 recoveries, 2 new deaths for 95 total fatalities |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/23/covid-19-update-71-new-cases-90-recoveries-2-new-deaths-for-95-total-fatalities |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=23 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200423095923/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/23/covid-19-update-71-new-cases-90-recoveries-2-new-deaths-for-95-total-fatalities |archivedate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n*New Zealand has reported three new cases (two confirmed and one probable). Three previous cases were also rescinded, keeping the total at 1,451. In addition, NZ authorities report 29 new recoveries, bringing the total to 1,065. Two further deaths are reported, bringing the death toll to 16.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/coronavirus/121213954/coronavirus-government-gives-latest-updates|title=Coronavirus: Two deaths, three new Covid-19 cases in New Zealand|work=Stuff|date=23 April 2020|accessdate=23 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200423015423/https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/coronavirus/121213954/coronavirus-government-gives-latest-updates|archive-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Singapore has reported 1,037 new cases, bringing the total to 11,178.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Clement |last2=Kurohi |first2=Rei |title=Foreign workers in dorms make up 982 of the 1,037 new Covid-19 cases |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/1037-new-coronavirus-cases-bringing-singapores-total-to-11178 |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=23 April 2020 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200423100503/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/1037-new-coronavirus-cases-bringing-singapores-total-to-11178|archive-date=23 April 2020}}</ref> In addition, a patient who had COVID-19 was found dead at a staircase landing, with the police investigating the cause of it.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ng |first1=Charmaine |title=Indian worker warded for Covid-19 dies after he was found at staircase landing of Khoo Teck Puat Hospital |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/1037-new-coronavirus-cases-bringing-singapores-total-to-11178 |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Ukraine reports 578 new cases and 13 new deaths, bringing the total numbers to 7,170 and 187 respectively, as well as a total of 504 recoveries.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e 7170 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 COVID-19 |url=https://www.facebook.com/moz.ukr/posts/1516763715153395 |website=facebook.com |publisher=Ministry of Healthcare of Ukraine |accessdate=23 April 2020 |language=uk |date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n<!--\n===24 April===\n===25 April===\n===26 April===\n===27 April===\n===28 April===\n===29 April===\n===30 April===\n-->\n\n== Summary ==\n\n===Timeline===\n\nCountries and territories that confirmed their first cases during April 2020:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5em;\"  | Date\n! style=\"width:25em;\" | Country or territory\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2 April\n| {{flagdeco|Malawi}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malawi|Malawi]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3 April\n| {{flagdeco|Falkland Islands}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Falkland Islands|Falkland Islands]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4 April\n| [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Western Sahara|Western Sahara]]{{efn|In the Moroccan-controlled part.}}\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5 April\n| {{flagdeco|Saint Pierre and Miquelon|local}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Pierre and Miquelon|Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|South Sudan}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Sudan|South Sudan]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6 April\n| {{