842/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/21/covid-19-57-new-cases-bringing-total-to-5482-three-new-fatalities-death-toll-now-at-92 |archivedate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n*In Morocco, 68 people, mainly staff, have tested positive for the coronavirus in the southern city of [[Ouarzazate]].<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*The Netherlands has reported 729 new cases, bringing the total to 34,134. Dutch health authorities have reported 165 deaths, bringing the death toll to 3,916.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 21 April reports\" />\n*New Zealand has reported 5 new cases (2 confirmed and 3 probable), bringing the total to 1,445 (1,107 confirmed and 338 probable). NZ authorities also report 32 new recoveries, bringing the total to 1,006. The country also reports a new death, bringing the death toll to 13.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=21 April 2020|access-date=21 April 2020|archive-date=21 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200421015622/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2020/04/coronavirus-five-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-new-zealand.html|first=Jamie|last=Ensor|title=Coronavirus: One death, five new cases of COVID-19 in New Zealand|work=Newshub|date=21 April 2020|accessdate=21 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200421020106/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2020/04/coronavirus-five-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-new-zealand.html|archive-date=21 April 2020}}</ref> In addition, a New Zealand traveller in Peru died after missing a repatriation flight, however this is not included in Ministry of Health figures.<ref name=\"NZ Herald Peru death\">{{cite news |last1=Henry |fir